channel.title: Oblivion 2 - need client developper and moderator
channel.description:
[size=36pt]Oblivion 2, where your dream story comes true! [/size]
[size=14pt]Hello everyone,
Introduction
Maybe you have seen oblivion 2 (partnership with froyoscape) in the development board. Our project is making good process but the only thing missing is a decent client. So we are still looking for one client sided programmer. Make sure u can show atleast something of urself otherwise your chances of becomming the client programmmer drops to 0%. [/size] [size=18pt]Oblivion 2: the storyline.[/size]
You start in a jail because you did something terribles but the problem is that you can't even remember it and the guard doesn't want to tell you it aswell. But then out of nowher old duke appears next to your cel door and tell the guard he must take you with him! The guard doesn't agree with that and they both die on a unexplained way. After that you must find yourself a way out of the manhole. When you get out duke stays right in front of you 100% alive. He didn't died for real but just used some loveed up magic cast to get away. Now you can start for da real job. After chosen your starter package you will be teleported to a random city in runescape. The problem is: you can't leave the city! Or you have to pay a big amount of money. You are sad because you want to go out and really enjoy the adventure! So you search for help by Hans. He will help you after you get lose friends with him. He will expain you that there is another way. The city keeper of lumbridge and any other city keeper let people through that gate when they did an hard job for the city. You will get a special note so the guards will let you pass. Now after this you start remembering why you were in jail and what Duke really needed from you and every time u do a quest u get closer to the answer!
[size=14pt]So how do i apply for client developper?[/size] Fill this in please. (Be honest.):
[code] Skype name/Msn name:
You experience with rsps programming(provide with links,names,pics):
How long are you programming rsps now:
Why do you want to join the Oblivion2 team:
Do you have any ideas we could use (if yes, what):
Can we trust you(to have it black on white):
Name a list of things u can do (to take the nubs out):
Will you be making fast and good process:
Any other thing u want to say:[/code]
[size=14pt]So how do i apply for moderator?[/size] Fill this in please. (Be honest.):
[code] Skype name/Msn name:
You experience with rsps staff(provide names etc...):
Do you know how to act in difficult situations?
Why do you want to join the Oblivion2 staff team:
Do you have any ideas we could use (if yes, what):
Can we trust you(to have it black on white):
Can you be trusted with powers ingame?
Will you act nice to other staff members and players?
Any other thing u want to say:[/code]
Be 100% honest we will check everything u said! We will contact the chosen one by a quote on here and a private message. I hope i informed you enough :)
Goodluck to you all!
To see more information about oblivion 2 check our dev thread: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,595538.40.html
To see more information about froyoscape check their thread: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,567011.0.html
Our team:
Head developer : Strucker (mr boogie) Programmers luna-scape (luna) Moderators : N/A
[size=18pt]Accepting requests for quests! [/size]

item.title: Oblivion 2 - need client developper and moderator
item.dc:creator: @nolan2131 nolan2131
item.description:
@nolan2131 wrote:

Applying for: Moderator

Name: Nolan Peterson
Age: 18

Skype name:

  • nolan-peterson

Your experience with rsps staff:

  • I was a moderator on Nividia for Encryption. http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,503577.msg3687604.html#msg3687604 <- Scroll down to locate my acceptance
  • I was a Co-developer on Final Judgement with Loveandpower.
  • I was on the development team of T.U.Pk.S with Ahram 4.
  • I was also an administrator/ developer for HamziX 614/ 317 but they only stayed open for a short period of time.

Do you know how to act in difficult situations?

  • Yes, I try to keep things mature, and I feel I act accordingly in difficult situations.

Why do you want to join the Oblivion2 staff team:

  • My project is at a stand point to be honest, and I find no more motivation for the time being. I want to expand my RSPS experience and I feel as if I can be an asset to your team.

Do you have any ideas we could use (if yes, what):

  • Not at the moment, although I will in the future, after I get a better understanding of what you are trying to create.

Can we trust you(to have it black on white):

  • Yes, my former colleagues will vouch for me.

Can you be trusted with powers ingame?

  • Yes, ^ same answer

Will you act nice to other staff members and players?

  • Yeah, I’m outgoing and I can get along with anyone.

Any other thing u want to say: Not much, regardless of your decision I hope all goes well, and good luck.

Read full topic
